cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses machine learning systems based on deep neural networks (DNNs) and their vulnerability to adversarial example attacks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography and security (cs.CR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as the paper proposes a configurable defense mechanism based on refining the DNN loss function. The other sub-categories are also relevant as they deal with topics such as security, image classification, and neural networks, which are discussed in the paper.
